{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct contains a table of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner."}],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsRef"}],"symbolKind":"struct","externalID":"s:4GLib14SourceFuncsRefV","roleHeading":"Structure","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsRef"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"SourceFuncsRef"},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol"]}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsRef"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For idle sources, the prepare and check functions always return "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to indicate that the source is always ready to be processed. The prepare","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function also returns a timeout value of 0 to ensure that the ","type":"text"},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t block (since that would be time wasted which could have been spent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"running the idle function)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For timeout sources, the prepare and check functions both return ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"if the timeout interval has expired. The prepare function also returns"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a timeout value to ensure that the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call doesn’t block too long","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and miss the next timeout."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For file descriptor sources, the prepare function typically returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"since it must wait until "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"text":" has been called before it knows whether","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"any events need to be processed. It sets the returned timeout to -1 to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"indicate that it doesn’t mind how long the ","type":"text"},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call blocks. In the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"check function, it tests the results of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call to see if the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"required condition has been met, and returns "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if so."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"